# Notes captured at vendoring time. Layer B vs Layer A discipline framing
# per arc/upstream-canonical/README.md.
notes: |
  This is the BFO 2020 CLIF axiomatization (Layer B per
  arc/upstream-canonical/README.md) — it defines the canonical FOL semantics
  of BFO ontology content (Continuant, Occurrent, IndependentContinuant,
  Process, Disposition, Quality, part_of, has_part, BFO Disjointness Map
  commitments, ternary parthood semantics, etc.).

  This is the COMPLEMENT to Layer A's owl-axiomatization.clif (which covers
  OWL primitives' FOL semantics — SubClassOf, Transitive, etc.). The two
  layers together provide the canonical semantic ground for OFBT's Phase 4+
  ARC content lift correctness:
    - Layer A licenses the lifted shape of OWL constructs (covered Phase 1+)
    - Layer B licenses the lifted shape of BFO ontology content (covered Phase 4)

  Phase 4 ARC content per `arc/core/bfo-2020.json` (40 Verified ARCEntry
  instances per Aaron-led parallel workstream) lifts under loaded ARC
  modules to FOL whose semantics matches this canonical Layer B CLIF. The
  `p4_bfo_clif_layer_b.fixture.js` corpus-before-code fixture exercises
  this lift-correctness parity per Phase 4 entry packet §3.2 + §3.4.

  License-verification ritual operates at Pass 2a vendoring time per
  ADR-010 + Q-4-G + the binding-immediately discipline. Aaron's Pass 2a
  vendoring closes [VERIFY] markers above; verification ritual run report
  attaches to Pass 2a commit per audit-trail-unity-per-surface.

  Future Phase 5+ vendorings (IAO, CCO modules etc.) inherit the same
  Layer B vendoring discipline established here; Phase-N vendoring sidecar
  authoring is a banked SME pattern per the Q-4-C ruling 2026-05-10's
  source-authority-chain extension banking.
